<P>
<a name="information"></a>
<B>The Information We Collect</B>
</P>

<P>
This Privacy Statement applies to all information collected or submitted via the Produce Reporter Co. web site.  Produce Reporter Co. is the sole owner of the information we collect on this site, and we will not use the information in ways different than what is disclosed in this notice.
</P>

<P>
<U>Business Information</U>
</P>

<P>
If you register to become a Blue Book Member, we will endeavor to collect information from you about your business, such as trade name, addresses, telephone and fax numbers, personnel names and background, financial details, the names of firms with which you regularly transact business, and credit/debit card information.  You may also submit information about other businesses and individuals, such as names, addresses, and your confidential trading experiences.  Similar information may be provided by Members and non-Members, at their option, while making an online order for products and services.  This optional information is treated separately from the required ordering information described below.  All registration information becomes a part of the Produce Reporter Co.'s database that is used by us in connection with providing our products and services to those entities and individuals utilizing Blue Book offerings.  For example, Produce Reporter Co. may use this personally identifiable information to create Online Business Reports for sale to the public or to license the use of such information to our third party business partners.
</P>

<P>
Our primary sources of information are businesses and individuals actively engaged in the wholesale fresh fruit and vegetable trading and transportation industries, as well as public records such as business registrations, Uniform Commercial Code filings and bankruptcy filings.  We believe that data quality is of the utmost importance.  As a result, we will implement exhaustive practices and policies to ensure that all data is as accurate, timely and complete as possible.
</P>

<P>
<U>Products and Services Order Information</U>
</P>

<P>
Members and non-Members may order certain Produce Reporter Co. products and services online.  When you place an order via this web site you will be required to provide personally identifiable information in connection with completing the Order Form.  The requested information may include such required data as your credit card information, your name, trade name, addresses, and telephone and fax numbers.  Such information will be used by Produce Reporter Co. and our third party online payment services partner,
<a href="https://seal.verisign.com/splash?form_file=fdf/splash.fdf&type=GOLD&sealid=0&dn=WWW.BLUEBOOKPRCO.COM&lang=en" target=external>VeriSign, Inc.
</a>, to complete your order, deliver the requested product or service, manage your account, provide customer service and comply with legal and regulatory requirements.  Neither Produce Reporter Co. nor VeriSign sells or voluntarily transfers this order information.  Produce Reporter Co. may, however, use such information for internal purposes such as market research and analysis.  Members and non-Members that order products and services are given the option to receive updates and newsletters about Produce Reporter Co. products and services as well as industry information.
</P>

<P>
<U>Cookies and IP Addresses</U>
</P>

<P>
Cookies are small files placed on your computer hard drive by programs and web servers.  The use of cookies is a standard practice in the Internet industry.  In order to function properly, this web site requires that you allow us to place cookies on your computer when you access and use the web site.  If you have cookies turned off, you will not be able to use all the functionality of this web site.  For your protection, Produce Reporter Co. uses security cookies to authenticate the identities of web site users.  We also use cookies to customize and improve our users' experience on the web site.
</P>

<P>
An Internet protocol ("IP") address is a set of numbers that is automatically assigned to your computer when you access the Internet.  Web servers identify your computer by the IP address assigned to it during your online session.  Produce Reporter Co. may use the IP addresses of our users to help diagnose problems with our servers and to administer the web site.
</P>

<P>
Produce Reporter Co. may also use cookies and/or IP addresses to measure certain traffic patterns, such as which areas of the web site you have visited.  We may use this information to personalize the content that you and other users will see on the web site.
</P>

<P>
<U>Email</U>
</P>

<P>
If you send us email, we will share that email with our customer service representative or other employee who is best suited to respond to your inquiry.  Once we have done our best to respond to your communication, we will either discard your email or, in certain instances, archive it.
</P>

<P>
Please note that the email functions on our web site do not provide for completely secure and private communications.  For example, as most email communications are not encrypted, such email messages may be accessed and viewed by other Internet users, without your knowledge and permission, while in transit to us.
</P>

<P>
<U>Other</U>
</P>

<P>
In the event that Produce Reporter Co. sells or acquires business assets or concerns, in whole or in part, Produce Reporter Co. may transfer all user information in conjunction with such sale or acquisition.  Other than the specific exceptions noted in this Privacy Statement, we do not sell, license or disclose personally identifiable user information collected about or from our users.
</P>

